ns1:Ransomware a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:comment """Ransomware is a type of malware from cryptovirology that threatens to publish the victim's personal data or permanently block access to it unless a ransom is paid. While some simple ransomware may lock the system without damaging any files, more advanced malware uses a technique called cryptoviral extortion. It encrypts the victim's files, making them inaccessible, and demands a ransom payment to decrypt them.

Source: https://dbpedia.org/page/Ransomware"""^^xsd:string ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ns1:Malware .

